For those of you in the Houston area, I'm giving a talk on JUnit later 
this month at the Lone Star Software Symposium.  

The presentation is a technical primer to using JUnit and the techniques 
of test-driven development.  It also covers example uses of Ant, Cactus, 
HttpUnit, and JUnitPerf, among others.

Details on the symposium are at:

    http://www.completeprogrammer.net/houston/

It would be great to meet some folks on this list!

Mike
